r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 127, 127); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>This year at Kumbh Mela, Persistent workedclosely with Nashik Rural Police to help them digitize their TrimbakeshwarControl Room. We worked jointly with Nashik Rural Police and provided a cloudbased Control Room Enabler, customized out of Accelerite&rsquo;s Emergency ResponseSolution. This was also an example of exemplary team work within Persistent,with the Government BU leading the engagement, BASE managing theonsite-deployment, and Accelerite providing the product / solution and overalltechnology ownership.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 127, 127); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>Our solution helped the Police authorities tovisualize their entire field deployment along with key landmarks, primaryroutes and evacuation routes on an easy-to-use dashboard. The solution enabledthe authorities to dynamically view various map layers, based on the situationat hand, thus helping them to swiftly respond to situations and manage theevent more efficiently.</em></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 127, 127); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em>Lending support to the Social media presence ofKumbhmela, Persistent&rsquo;s eMee team took complete ownership of the social mediastrategy, execution and analytics for the official Kumbhmela handle, includingcontent creation. The challenge was to maintain public interest in anon-celebrity topic such as the development works done by the cityadministration, while providing critical updates and being the eyes and ears ofthe administration. It was also important to appear non-partisan, non-politicaland steer clear of controversial topics. The eMee team deployed its SocialRadar, which was previously used for Chennai Express, SMJ and is now beingeffectively used by the Pune Smart City team.</em></span></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 127, 127); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em>Persistent is extremely proud to contribute tothe success of Kumbh Mela</em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><img alt=\"khumb m.PNG\" src=\"https://pi.persistent.co.in/ExecutiveAnnouncements/PublishingImages/Lists/Posts/AllPosts/khumb%20m.PNG\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\"><em>Warm Regards,</em></span><br />\r\n			<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 105, 153); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Mritunjay Singh</span><br />\r\n			<em><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Executive Director &amp; Chief Operations Officer</span></em></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><em><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\"><img alt=\"Capture.PNG\" src=\"https://pi.persistent.co.in/ExecutiveAnnouncements/PublishingImages/Lists/Posts/AllPosts/Capture.PNG\" style=\"margin: 5px;\" /></span></em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Persistent Systems | Partners in Innovation<br />\r\n			<a href=\"http://www.persistent.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 105, 153);\">www.persistent.com</span></a></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','cxo_messages',0,38,51,'und',0,'<p>ghfghd</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','cxo_messages',0,40,54,'und',0,'<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">As the Pakistan establishment closes in on terror group Jaish-e- Mohammed and its founder Maulana Masood Azhar - who India believes planned both the Pathankot air base attack and the strike on the Indian consulate in Mazar-e-Sharif, Afghanistan - one man would have reason to smile. National Security Advisor Ajit Doval.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">In 1994 when Masood Azhar was accidentally caught in Srinagar, most agencies would disregard him as a small catch till Ajit Doval walked into the scene.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Azhar was 26 and was travelling on a false Portuguese passport, posing as a journalist who compiled a magazine for the Harkat-ul Mujahdeen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Painstaking investigation and intelligence gathering by Ajit Doval and his team unearthed just how big Azhar was in the terror infrastructure of Pakistan. Also that he was sent by Pakistan&#39;s Inter-Services Intelligence or ISI to get the groups Harkut-ul- Ansar and Harkat-ul-Mujahideen together to carry out spectacular terror&nbsp; attacks in the Kashmir Valley and other parts of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">One of his team members then - Asif Ibrahim - continues to be with him. Now as the Prime Minister&#39;s Special Envoy on Terrorism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Ajit Doval&#39;s team, which comprised Asif Ibrahim, who is the Prime Minister Special Envoy on Terrorism, and Avinash Mohananey, now Director General of Police of Sikkim, alerted New Delhi to initiate remedial action.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"ins_instory_dv\">\r\n<div class=\"ins_instory_dv_cont\"><span class=\"storyimage smallfullwidth inlineimage\" data-aop=\"image\"><span class=\"image\" data-attrib=\"Provided by NDTV 24x7\" data-caption=\"\" data-id=\"78\" data-m=\"{&quot;i&quot;:78,&quot;p&quot;:75,&quot;n&quot;:&quot;openModal&quot;,&quot;t&quot;:&quot;articleImages&quot;,&quot;o&quot;:3}\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"loaded\" data-src=\"{&quot;default&quot;:{&quot;load&quot;:&quot;default&quot;,&quot;w&quot;:&quot;65&quot;,&quot;h&quot;:&quot;40&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;//img-s-msn-co